 of ft t\ngurc as most people expected. There j\ni a deep down feeling in the financial\nistrict that the general election will be f\nemocratic in results and that the Roose- j\nelt ticket in New York will be over-helmed\nunder an avalanche of opposi* _\non votes as great as that which buried t\n'olger when Orover Cleveland was electd\ngovernor of the Empire state. c\nAt the same time there is a secret fear f\nRoolevelt which tends to keep down t\nnthusfasm and repress hostile talk. The _\nlay seems to be to keep your mouth\nhut and express your feelings at the\noils. The people in Wall street are prone C\ncut out political discussion except in n\nle confidence of the back office or In the\ntuba, where .they are in no danger of\notting into the papers or attracting ovcrliicli\nattention.\nThis streak of yellow, or, as they prefer t\ncall it, discretion. Is an uncertain sen- i\nment and party leaders are not quite 5\n?adv to express opinions as to how much n\n-eight to attach to it in making up csti- q\nlates. o\nInterviews Called Flubdub.\n\nThe burden 01 tnc cannea interviews i hich\nfind their way into print these days B\nthat the business outlook is brighten- i\nlg and that if wo only have a little\natience things will pan out all right,\nhat is a beautiful sentiment and should y\nII the hearts of the populace with rosy\nopes.\nUnfortunately, however, these interlews\ndo not agree with the great mass\nf known facts and is classified as flubub,\nsweet to the ear, but really mean- S\nig nothing. It savors very much of a\nhristian Science attempt to talk the\nlarket and the situation up. And as\nverybody knows, conversation is cheap, J\nbout the cheapest thing on the list. In\nood times conversation is occasionally 0\nranstnutahle into coin, but not now. n\nThe bulletins make mention of about\nle fastest work on record In the way of 11\nreatlng credit structure. It is the taking w\nver of a little spur of a railroad' running\nrom E^vansvllle, Ind., out into the neigh-\norlng swamp, a property having a capaiizatlon\nof $50,000. The Big Four ac- n\nuired the streak of rust on a ninety- ii\nIne-year lease, immediately swelled its C:\napital to $500,000 and on the strength of\nhe deal had its new subsidiary issue\n5.000,000 bonds, which the Big Four is to\nnderwrlte. c\nh\nKilled as Cars Drop Thirty Feet.\nBLMIRA, X. Y., October 8.?Eastbound\n<ackawanna passenger train No. 14\nraslied into the rear end of a local 1'\nreighj. train pulling into a siding\nlie Chemung River bridge, just west\nf Waverly, early today. .The caboose\nfas demolished and two freight cars\nhrown down a thirty-foot embankment. d\ni. man thought to be Emmet Taylor of 8\nlean, who was in one car with a g]\nrotting horse, was instantly killed. The\nassengers were badly jolted, but none\n?as hurt. a'\n11\nWoman Drops Dead on Farm.\nDETROIT. Mich.. October if.-Mr*. J\namurl Denbits of Chicago, dropped dead tj\n\"'ay of heart disease on a farm near at\ne. 'Mt>; tfidti. si\n4\nIE OF PRICES\nBusiness October 8 at\nitock Exchange.\nellaneoni Shares.\ns highest, lowest and closing: prices.\n:urlttes sold on the New York Stock\nices ajJB also *lven for the full year\nt Week coiling Oct. 8 i\nSale*. High. Low. Close, fetch\n105.100 66% 64*4 66%4- 1%\n3.100 40 48 40 4- 1\n4.900 85% 62% 04 1%\nth eoo 4% 4*4 4%+\npfd.... 40O 21% 20\\ 21\nl.OOu 18% 18 18*4- *4\n500 12*4 12 12\n1.000 34 32 33%4- 3*4\n4.200 39% 36% 37%?\npfd 1.000 104% 103 103 4-\n48.150 70% 67% 69%4- 2\na 1.400 102% 101% 101%?\n9.300 117% 111% 116 2%\n200 115 112 115\n400 94% 93*4 94%4- 2\n2,200 30% 28% 30%-t- 2\n5.200 40% 39% 40%-h\n34.300 101% 99% 10?>%\n600 100% 100% l0O%\ninc..... 4,000 115 112% 115 4- 2%\na? rt?n 1A?1 1 1 iktiH K,\nn,AUM IV *4 r R\nTrans.. 11.100 77% 76% 70S,-\n22.100 196% 19.1 194%+\n9.000 35% 34 34 St S\nd 475 105 104% 105\nhlo 72,200 82% 79% 81%+ 2%\n200 35 35 35 3\n2.8(9) 24% 23% 24 4-\npfd 2,900 4SVi 47 47%+\n36.O00 123% 121 122%+\npfd... 9O0 149% 148 148%+\nt 2.900 148% 147 147%?\